        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens model picker provider catalog projection: live provider catalog setup now reads provider ids, aliases, hook aliases, env vars, catalog hooks, and normalized catalog rows through bounded readers so one unreadable runtime provider row does not hide healthy live catalog rows\n- previous refresh also hardened web search install catalog projection for official external web-search catalog rows\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `56980ab300b8ce8898324cefd981f53acbac8a6c`, proven on `origin/main` at `069ea7942d254d5fe4ff99e0cfb38ebaa25d623e`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/flows/model-picker.provider-catalog.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 1 file passed, 2 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/flows/model-picker.provider-catalog.ts src/flows/model-picker.provider-catalog.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/flows/model-picker.provider-catalog.ts src/flows/model-picker.provider-catalog.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean before commit on the provider-picker catalog slice\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run -provider blacksmith-testbox -shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`: blocked before remote execution because Blacksmith is not authenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required)\n- scrubbed touched files/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, provider/runtime/channel/plugin registry projections, model/provider install catalog projections, web search install catalog projection, and model picker provider catalog projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable env vars, unreadable install/provider metadata, unreadable catalog hooks, or unreadable catalog rows while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, based on `origin/main` at `069ea7942d254d5fe4ff99e0cfb38ebaa25d623e`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: after the model picker provider catalog slice and final rebase, ran focused formatting, commit diff check, linting, Vitest, synthetic/private-name scrub, autoreview, and attempted the Blacksmith-backed changed gate listed in Verification.\n\nEvidence after fix: `model-picker.provider-catalog.test.ts` seeds an unreadable `fuzzplugin` discovery provider id while proving the healthy `mockplugin` live catalog remains visible and still uses the fast env-key resolver path. `web-search-install-catalog.test.ts` also covers the previous refresh by keeping a healthy `mockplugin` install entry visible after unreadable `fuzzplugin` catalog/provider metadata.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed live provider discovery/catalog metadata no longer aborts preferred-provider catalog loading before healthy rows are reached; malformed official external web-search catalog/provider metadata no longer aborts setup/install catalog resolution before healthy rows are reached.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate did not run because the local Blacksmith CLI is unauthenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required). AWS Crabbox broad gate was not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted provider-picker/web-search install catalog surfaces plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
